~The American Revolutionary War was fought from the years 1775-1781.`  The American colonists declared their independence from the British empire on July 4, 1776.`  Even though there had been some fighting before this date, the Declaration of Independence marked the official start of the war.`  General George Washington (who had dentures made of wood) was the commander of the colonial forces.`  He led the colonial army to victory over the British and became the first president of the United States of America.`  He is known as the "father" of our country.`

~Abraham Lincoln was the 16th president of the United States of America.`  He served as president from 1860-1865.`  He was president of the Union during the American Civil War.`  This war began in 1861 when the southern states attempted to secede from the Union.`  Jefferson Davis became the first and only president of these southern "confederate" states.`  Davis and the people of the south felt that their economy, lifestyle and basic philosophy of life differed from the north so greatly that the Union had to be dissolved.`  Lincoln felt that the Union had to be preserved at all costs including war.`  The Civil War featured many bloody battles such as:  Bull Run, Antietam and Gettysburg.`  In 1863 (in the middle of the Civil War) Lincoln issued the Emancipation Proclamation which outlawed slavery.`   The north finally won the war in 1865, ending the bloodiest conflict in American history.`

~In April of 1865, President Abraham Lincoln was assassinated by John Wilkes Booth.`  Lincoln was watching a play at Ford's Theater when he was shot by Booth.`  Lincoln became the first U.S. president to be killed while holding office.`  Due to Lincoln's death vice-president Andrew Johnson became president.`

